    </equation><para id="import-auto-id2688907">One mole of a nuclide <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mi>A</m:mi></m:msup><m:mi>X</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"" lSup { size 8{A} } X} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> has a mass of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>A</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{A} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> grams, so that one mole of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mtext>137</m:mtext></m:msup><m:mtext>Cs</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"" lSup { size 8{"137"} } "Cs"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> has a mass of 137 g. A mole has <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>02 </m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>23</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{6 "." "02 " times "10" rSup { size 8{"23"} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> nuclei. Thus the mass of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mtext>137</m:mtext></m:msup><m:mtext>Cs</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"" lSup { size 8{"137"} } "Cs"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> released was</para><equation id="eip-187"><m:math>
