    <exercise id="fs-id1439074" type="conceptual-questions"><problem id="fs-id3250447">
    <para id="import-auto-id3305522">Radioactivity depends on the nucleus and not the atom or its chemical state. Why, then, is one kilogram of uranium more radioactive than one kilogram of uranium hexafluoride?</para>
