   <title>Construct Your Own Problem</title>
</para>
<para id="eip-id2061631">Consider the generation of electricity by a radioactive isotope in a space probe, such as described in <link target-id="eip-660"/>. Construct a problem in which you calculate the mass of a radioactive isotope you need in order to supply power for a long space flight. Among the things to consider are the isotope chosen, its half-life and decay energy, the power needs of the probe and the length of the flight.
